body:
Context: https://tour.golang.org/basics/3

It will be really user friendly if the Go tour uses left and right arrow keys to go to previous and next page. It can be easily implemented in javascript like 

```javascript

function leftArrowPressed() {
   // links to prev
}

function rightArrowPressed() {
   // links to next
}

document.onkeydown = function(evt) {
    evt = evt || window.event;
    switch (evt.keyCode) {
        case 37:
            leftArrowPressed();
            break;
        case 39:
            rightArrowPressed();
            break;
    }
};

```
